@zhenlin-pay2 Yes, `@JsonCreator` is for indicating which Creator (constructor or factory method) should be used.

But in case of `abstract` classes, introspection is skipped with assumption that they cannot be created (being abstract). But while true for Constructors (which really cannot be used to actually create instances), Factory methods would be useful (being `static` and thereby could be called).

What would be useful here would be actual minimized unit test (under `tofix` package, for branch `2.18` or `2.19`) that'd fail. It'd be easier for someone to look into how to fix the problem.
